==English==

===Etymology===
From Latin '''[[dividere]]''', to divide

===Transitive verb===
{{en-verb|divid|ing}}

# To split or separate (something) into two or more parts.
# To [[share]] (something) by dividing it.
#:''How shall we '''divide''' this pie?''
# (''arithmetic'') For a given number (the [[dividend]]), to calculate the number (the [[quotient]]) by which a second multiply a second number (the [[divisor]]) by to produce the dividend.
#: ''If you '''divide''' 6 by 3, you get 2.''

====Synonyms====
*(''split or separate into two or more parts'') [[cut up]], [[partition]], [[separate]], [[split]], [[split up]]
*(''share by dividing'') [[divi up]], [[divide up]], [[share]], [[share out]]

